Clone the repository from https://github.com/ampcusunified/calamari to your local system
git clone https://github.com/ampcusunified/calamari.git
Clone the calamari models repository from https://github.com/Calamari-OCR/calamari_models to your local system
git clone https://github.com/Calamari-OCR/calamari_models.git
INSTALL Python 3.6.1
The suggested method is to install calamari into a virtual environment using pip:
virtualenv -p python3 PATH_TO_VENV_DIR (e. g. virtualenv calamari_venv)
source PATH_TO_VENV_DIR/bin/activate
pip install calamari_ocr
pip install tensorflow 
To install the package from its source, download the source code and run:
python setup.py install
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install scikit-image==0.15.0
pip install scipy==1.3.0
Go the directory of the source files and run predict.py with arguments required
python predict.py --checkpoint yourpath.ckpt --files yourpath\*.png
(eg:python predict.py --checkpoint C:\Users\Lakshmi.UNIFIEDIT\Documents\GitHub\calamari_models\antiqua_modern\4.ckpt --files C:\Users\Lakshmi.UNIFIEDIT\Pictures\calamaripic\*.png)

